description: 1967 Austin-Healey BJ8 Mark III- Utah Showroom  The 3000 Mark III was launched in October 1963, and remained in production until the end of 1967, when manufacture of Austin-Healeys ceased. Only one further car was built in March 1968. Designated the BJ8, the 2+2 Mark III was the most powerful and luxurious of the big Healeys, with a standard walnut-veneer dash, wind-up windows, and a 150 hp I-6 cylinder engine. Added power came from a new camshaft and valve springs, twin SU 2" HD8 carburettors, and a new exhaust system design. Servo-assisted brakes were also standard. Options remained otherwise the same, except that the standard interior trim was downgraded to Ambla vinyl, with leather as an extra.  This beautifully restored "Big Healey" is nicely presented in Classic White and features genuine wire wheels with knock-offs. It has correctly detailed engine bay, interior and trunk.

description: 1960 Austin Healey 3000 BT7:

The Austin-Healey 3000 was introduced in 1959, replacing the Austin-Healey 100-6. The original 3000 was built from March 1959 to March 1961 as models BN7 Mark I (2-seater) and BT7 Mark I (2+2 version). It featured a straight 6 cylinder engine, 2912 cc , with twin SU carburetors and Girling front disc brakes. Wire wheels, overdrive gearbox, laminated windscreen, heater, adjustable steering column, detachable hard top, and two-tone paint were available as options.
A total of 13,650 Mark I’s were made (2,825 BN7, and 10,825 BT7).

This 1960 Austin Healy is a beautiful example of a car that can be shown in special events or driven around town for pure pleasure. The odometer shows 58,000 miles on it. We cannot verify this to be the actual mileage  but it is likely the case considering its current condition.  The car is in perfect mechanical condition with a very strong engine and four speed transmission with a fully functioning Over Drive.  The interior is leather and in excellent condition.  The car was originally red but was painted Healy Blue sometime back by the previous owner who had the car for over 20 years and lived in Los Gatos. The current owner purchased the car in 2012 and had all the Chrome either replaced or redone and painted under the hood and under the car the same Blue. It is now in the shape you see in the pictures.    Please call for more information.

description: 1967 Austin-Healey 3000 Mark III    Chassis No. H-BJ8-L/35828  Engine No. 29K-RU-H/10608    The Ultimate Big Healey Model, with Factory Overdrive  Numbers-Matching Engine per British Motor Industry Heritage Trust  Ideal Driver Quality Sports Convertible, Desirable BJ8 Series  Presented in Striking Colors & Complete with all Weather Equipment     The last generation of the Big Healey was powered by a 2.9-liter SOHC inline six-cylinder engine that could produce 148 horsepower and was coupled to a four-speed manual transmission that had an overdrive unit. Major styling enhancements, which also improved the aerodynamics, were also done to the Austin-Healey. A wraparound windscreen was installed, and the doors now had roll-down windows; gone were side-curtains. A removable rear-window panel was also featured, and handling was also greatly improved, thanks to a stiffer anti-roll bar up front and modified shock settings.    The Mark III offered here was built April 18-19, 1966 and dispatched on the 27th, destined for Chicago, Illinois in Healey Blue paint with Blue trim and hood. Factory equipment included wire wheels, heater, adjustable steering column, whitewall tires, blue tonneau cover, laminated windscreen and overdrive gearbox. Chassis #35828 now displays older paint and upholstery, never fully restored, but rather maintained as needed - Ideal for those seeking a numbers-matching and very spirited driver. This BJ8 is complete with Owner's Manual, convertible top, matching boot cover and spare tire assembly. Furthermore, correct Michelin XWX tires and driving lamps compliment the ensemble. British Motor Heritage Trust Heritage Document Wallet confirms all original factory specifications.    As one of the most revered and iconic British sports cars of timeless beauty, this Austin-Healey 3000 Mk III offers its new owner a joy to drive and makes for a great car to use in many ways. These beautiful and user friendly machine are becoming widely recognized as one of the most bang for the buck collectibles in the market!
